{"description":"The {{ExplodedGraphWalker}} does not update symbolic values associated to symbols when accessed using {{this.}} or {{super.}}, but only when a simple identifier is used.\r\n\r\nConsequently, the following code will raise a FP on RSPEC-2583:\r\n{code}\r\nabstract class A {\r\n\r\n  private long x;\r\n\r\n  public void decrementX() {\r\n    if (this.x \u003e 0) {\r\n      this.x--;\r\n      if (this.x \u003d\u003d 0) { // FP S2583\r\n        doSomething();\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  abstract void doSomething();\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nWhile the completely equivalent code stay correctly silent:\r\n{code}\r\nabstract class A {\r\n\r\n  private long x;\r\n\r\n  public void decrementX() {\r\n    if (x \u003e 0) {\r\n      x--;\r\n      if (x \u003d\u003d 0) { // \u003c-- No issue\r\n        doSomething();\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  abstract void doSomething();\r\n}\r\n{code}","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"4.14"}